| Criteria | Why this model works |
|---|---|
| **Resume value** | It's a **Sentence-Transformer** from Hugging Face — recruiters and PFA supervisors recognise this immediately as real NLP/DL work |
| **Not too advanced** | You're using a **pre-trained model** (no fine-tuning needed). You call `model.encode(text)` and get vectors. That's it |
| **Multilingual** | Handles **French + English** job descriptions out of the box — perfect since your data has both |
| **Lightweight** | 12 layers, 118M params, produces **384-d vectors** — runs fine on CPU, no GPU needed |
| **Industry-relevant** | Sentence-Transformers + cosine similarity is a real technique used in production recommendation systems |
| **Explainable** | You can clearly explain it in your report: *"We encode job descriptions into dense vectors and rank by cosine similarity"* |

**What you'll be able to say in interviews:**
> *"I built a semantic job recommendation engine using Sentence-Transformers (paraphrase-multilingual-MiniLM-L12-v2) to encode job descriptions into 384-dimensional embeddings, then ranked them using cosine similarity combined with keyword-based skill matching."*

